==English==
''Archaic''
===Etymology===
[[Latin]] ''[[thebaicus]]''
===Adjective===
'''Thebaic''' or '''thebaic'''
# [[Theban]]; of or pertaining to [[Thebes]]
# of or pertaining to the [[Bible]] as preserved by the Egyptian Theban [[Wikipedia:Copt|Copt]]s.
# of or pertaining to [[opium]]; intoxicated with opium
#:''A circle of junkies sat in a '''thebaic''' haze.''
# (''of a hallucination'') prone to be experienced under the influence of opium
#:''[[Wikipedia:Samuel Taylor Coleridge|Coleridge]] drew inspiration from his '''thebaic''' fantasies.''

